Used to think Shake Shack burgers were overrated, but there’s something about the simplicity of the burger, the taste of the patty and the dense, fluffy butteriness of the bun that just makes it a quality fast food sandwich. In contrast to Five Guys, Shake Shack patties actually have flavor and they’re not overly laden with fat. The result is you get a solid meat burger. Everything else on the menu is decent, though I think they should retire their korean chicken sandwich and leave that to the pros. The milkshakes are delicious. And the grilled cheese sandwich is perfection.

It was sad experiencing such bad customer service. Someone else hands my food, not a hi, he voiced like it was a bother to hand me my food, and miss pronounces my last name, and not a sorry.
A year into the pandemic, multiple staff members have not figured out that you have to wear your mask over your nose. Totally unacceptable. Unsafe.

Food: Shake Shack burgers are one one of the best I've ever had. They're a bit smaller than Johnny Rockets and Five Guys and comparable to a Big Mac or In 'n Out burgers. It's always juicy but a favorite of mine is the shroom burger. Cheese quite literally oozes out of the burger, it's fantastic. Their shakes are also a favorite of mine, Chik Fil - A's aree better but it's still an upgrade from McDonalds shakes. I also like that you can add malt to the shakes.  Pricing: Definitely more expensive than fast food, a burger, shake, and fries will get you close to $20.  The aforementioned Shroom burger is close to $8.  Experience: If you go during a time when there are events in the area, be prepared to wait a few minutes. This is a popular place, though weekday lunch and dinner are pretty average and the wait time is close to 10 minutes. Bathroom was clean when I went and the dining area had plenty of space, but it's a fast food place, adjust your expectations accordingly.
